<meta property="og:description" content="We live in a world of scarce resources. Yet how well we utilize these resources depends on day-to-day decisions that we make. The economic concept of 'supply and demand' helps us understand the decisions of others and ourselves. In this module, students learn the basics of sound decision-making by examining choices and scarcity and appreciating how trade creates value for both parties through the principles of ‘comparative advantage’ and ‘free trade’. " />
